issue.title: feat: Remove CNTK functionality and replace with ONNX

Currently the ImageFeaturizer uses CNTK models. This PR replaces this underlying dependency with ONNX models, effectively removing usage of CNTK from the library.

Associated changes:
Create ONNXHub for referring to predefined SynapseML models in the cloud
Directly use ONNX-ML protobuf classes for splitting models at internal nodes

issue.title: [systemtest] Make `testUpgradeKafkaWithoutVersion` to run with parameters from yaml
issue.body:
Signed-off-by: Lukas Kral <lukywill16@gmail.com>

### Type of change

- Enhancement

### Description

Currently the `testUpgradeKafkaWithoutVersion` runs with hardcoded values, which points to Strimzi `0.23.0`. But that version wasn't built for other architectures like `ppc64le` or `s390x`, which makes running this test on different arch environment impossible.

This PR changes the `testUpgradeKafkaWithoutVersion` to run with parameters from upgrade yaml.

As part of this, I added `UpgradeKafkaVersion`, which just represents Kafka with version, LMFV and IBPV. I could go with `TestKafkaVersion`, but that contains a lot more variables than we need and also it's kinda impossible to create that variable with specific values like `null` or `""`, which is needed in our tests.

We will need to refactor the upgrade tests, with all the names of each field in the yamls (and corresponding variable names inside the `UpgradeDowngradeData`), but it's for different PR and it will need some better idea, how to do it.

### Checklist

- [ ] Make sure all tests pass

issue.title: [systemtest] Make `testUpgradeKafkaWithoutVersion` to run with parameters from yaml
issue.body:
Signed-off-by: Lukas Kral <lukywill16@gmail.com>

### Type of change

- Enhancement

### Description

Currently the `testUpgradeKafkaWithoutVersion` runs with hardcoded values, which points to Strimzi `0.23.0`. But that version wasn't built for other architectures like `ppc64le` or `s390x`, which makes running this test on different arch environment impossible.

This PR changes the `testUpgradeKafkaWithoutVersion` to run with parameters from upgrade yaml.

As part of this, I added `UpgradeKafkaVersion`, which just represents Kafka with version, LMFV and IBPV. I could go with `TestKafkaVersion`, but that contains a lot more variables than we need and also it's kinda impossible to create that variable with specific values like `null` or `""`, which is needed in our tests.

We will need to refactor the upgrade tests, with all the names of each field in the yamls (and corresponding variable names inside the `UpgradeDowngradeData`), but it's for different PR and it will need some better idea, how to do it.

### Checklist

- [ ] Make sure all tests pass

issue.title: [systemtest] Make `testUpgradeKafkaWithoutVersion` to run with parameters from yaml
issue.body:
Signed-off-by: Lukas Kral <lukywill16@gmail.com>

### Type of change

- Enhancement

### Description

Currently the `testUpgradeKafkaWithoutVersion` runs with hardcoded values, which points to Strimzi `0.23.0`. But that version wasn't built for other architectures like `ppc64le` or `s390x`, which makes running this test on different arch environment impossible.

This PR changes the `testUpgradeKafkaWithoutVersion` to run with parameters from upgrade yaml.

As part of this, I added `UpgradeKafkaVersion`, which just represents Kafka with version, LMFV and IBPV. I could go with `TestKafkaVersion`, but that contains a lot more variables than we need and also it's kinda impossible to create that variable with specific values like `null` or `""`, which is needed in our tests.

We will need to refactor the upgrade tests, with all the names of each field in the yamls (and corresponding variable names inside the `UpgradeDowngradeData`), but it's for different PR and it will need some better idea, how to do it.

### Checklist

- [ ] Make sure all tests pass
